The '''''Children's Illustrated Encyclopedia''''' is an [[encyclopedia]] marketed for use by [[children]] ages 7-17.<ref>{{cite web|title=Review: DK Children’s Illustrated Encyclopedia|url=http://booklistonline.com/DK-Children-s-Illustrated-Encyclopedia/pid=1041481|publisher=Booklist|accessdate=28 October 2014}}</ref> The single-volume work emphasizes [[visual aid|visuals]] like [[illustration]]s, [[photograph]]s, [[map]]s, and [[timeline]]s over breadth of coverage, and entries are supplemented by an official [[website]] and [[URL]]s to third party resources.<ref name=rr>{{cite journal|work=Reference Reviews|last=Thebridge|title=Children's Illustrated Encyclopedia (7th ed.) |first=Stella|volume=25|issue=3|date=2011}}</ref><ref name=slj2>{{cite journal|work=School Library Journal|last1=Carcich|last2=Grabarek|last3=Minkel|first1=Mary Ann|first2=Daryl|first3=Walter|volume=47|issue=2|page=78|date=February 2001|title=Children's Illustrated Encyclopedia (Book Review)}}</ref><ref name=bookpage>{{cite web|work=BookPage|title=DK Children's Illustrated Encyclopedia [book review]|url=http://bookpage.com/reviews/269-dk-childrens-illustrated-encyclopedia#.VE6IzPldVr8|date=December 1998|last=Bennett|first=Kathy}}</ref> It is in its seventh edition, published since 2010 by [[Dorling Kindersley]].<ref name=slj>{{cite journal|work=School Library Journal|last=Auerbach|first=Barbara|title=Khurana, Ashwin, ed. Children's Illustrated Encyclopedia |date=August 2010|volume=56|issue=8|page=68}}</ref> It was shortlisted for a 2001 [[Blue Peter Book Award]] in the "Best Book of Knowledge" category.<ref name=worldcat>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldcat.org/title/dorling-kindersley-childrens-illustrated-encyclopedia/oclc/68262797|work=WorldCat|title=Dorling Kindersley children's illustrated encyclopedia|accessdate=27 October 2014}}</ref>

