{{Infobox book | italic title = <!--(see above)--> | name = Fatawa-e-Razvia {{Nastaliq|فتاویٰ رضویہ}} | image = Fatawarazavia.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = | author = [[Ahmed Raza Khan]] | audio_read_by = | title_orig = | orig_lang_code = | title_working = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = [[India]] | language = [[Urdu]], [[Persian language|Persian]], [[Arabic]] and one fatwa in [[English language|English]] | series = | release_number = | subject = | genre = | set_in = | published = 1911 to 2005 | publisher = many publisher of [[pakistan]] and [[india]] | publisher2 = | pub_date = | english_pub_date = | media_type = | pages = 30 volumes, 22000+ pages، Six thousand eight hundred forty questions and answers | awards = | isbn = 2-7451-7204-2 | isbn_note = Arabic ed | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | native_wikisource = | wikisource = | notes = | exclude_cover = | website = }} {{Barelvi}} '''Fatawa-e-Razvia''' or Fatawa-e-Radaviyyah is the main [[fatwa]] book of [[Barelvi]] Muslims <ref>http://library.uos.edu.pk:8000/cgi-bin/koha/opac-detail.pl?biblionumber=34385&shelfbrowse_itemnumber=37915</ref><ref>"Barelvi - Oxford Reference". oxfordreference.com. Retrieved 2014-09-24</ref>{{failed verification|date=August 2015}} authored by 19th century [[Sunni]] [[Islamic scholar]] [[Ahmed Raza Khan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.milligazette.com/news/4249-jamia-rizvia-of-bareilly-to-be-upgraded-to-a-university|title=Jamia Rizvia of Bareilly to be upgraded to a university|work=milligazette.com}}</ref><ref name="Noorie2008">{{cite book|author=Maulana Shakir Noorie|title=What is Sacrifice?: Qurbani kya hai?|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IbmMBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA12|date=10 October 2008|publisher=Sunni Dawate Islami|pages=12–|id=GGKEY:G6T13NU1Q2T}}</ref>
The Fatawa-e-Razvia was discussed by [[Arun Shourie]] in his book, The World of Fatwas or the Sharia in Action <ref>(2012, {{ISBN|9789350293423}}).</ref> Its 12 volume were first published by [[Ahmed Raza Khan]]'s brother at Hasani press and only two volumes of various Fatawa's were published during the lifetime of author.<ref name="Sanyal2012">{{cite book|author=Usha Sanyal|title=Ahmad Riza Khan Barelwi: In the Path of the Prophet|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uXvZAQAAQBAJ&pg=PT56|date=1 December 2012|publisher=Oneworld Publications|isbn=978-1-78074-189-5|pages=56–}}</ref>
The book is published in 30 volumes by various [[Sunni]] publications. It contains solution to daily problems from religion to business and from war to marriage.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jagran.com/uttar-pradesh/bareilly-city-dargah-ala-hazrat-fatva-razabia-is-encyclopedia-of-fatvas-11887041.html|title=Dargah Ala Hazrat: Fatva Razabia is encyclopedia of Fatvas|date=18 December 2014|work=jagran}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dawateislami.net/islam/downloads/details.php?id=10_Fatawa-Razawiyyah|title=Islamic Speeches Free Download - Dawateislami|author=I.T Department of Dawat-e-Islami|work=dawateislami.net}}</ref><ref name="Singh2012">{{cite book|author=David Emmanuel Singh|title=Islamization in Modern South Asia: Deobandi Reform and the Gujjar Response|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=upk5AgAAQBAJ&pg=PA32|year=2012|publisher=Walter de Gruyter|isbn=978-1-61451-246-2|pages=32–}}</ref> [[Raza Academy]] was first to publish its various volumes in 1985.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.razaacademy.com/index.php/about-us |title=About us |author= |work=razaacademy.com |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150716015556/http://www.razaacademy.com/index.php/about-us |archivedate=2015-07-16 |df= }}</ref>
