'''Lifetime Lab''' is a visitor centre located in the old [[Victorian architecture|Victorian]] waterworks along the [[River Lee]] in the city of [[Cork (city)|Cork]]. Cork City Council undertook a restoration and conservation project,<ref>{{cite web|title=Cork City Energy Agency » Projects » Lifetime Lab|url=http://www.corkcity.ie/services/environmentrecreation/corkcityenergyagency/projects/lifetimelab/|publisher=Cork City Council|accessdate=28 September 2014}}</ref> completed in 2005, to transform the industrial buildings into a new centre focused on environmental issues, science, education, and Cork’s industrial heritage.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lifetime Lab at Old Cork Waterworks|url=http://www.corkheritageopenday.ie/thebuildings/educationalbuildings/buildings/mainbody,10802,en.html|publisher=Cork Heritage|accessdate=28 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Lifetime Lab|url=http://www.westcorkeducationcentre.com/resources/lifetime-lab/|publisher=West Cork Education Centre|accessdate=28 September 2014}}</ref>
