'''Swedish Master Series''' (''Swedish Master-serien'' or ''Mästar-serien'') is a set of [[hockey cards]] produced by a Swedish company between 1969 and 1971. At least two sets were produced and distributed in Europe. The first set was for the 1969-70 hockey season and the second set was for the 1970-71 season. Both sets included players from Swedish teams and national teams from other countries. [[Ken Dryden]] was featured in both sets prior to his debut in the [[National Hockey League]].<ref>http://cgi.ebay.com/1970-Swedish-Masterserien-26-Ken-Dryden-Canada_W0QQitemZ110445710030QQcmdZViewItemQQptZUS_Hockey_Trading_Cards?hash=item19b713cace</ref>

